    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">11</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Summary</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Key Takeaways: Understanding 'Texican'</h2><ul><li>'Texican' refers to Mexican citizens living in Texas during 1820-1836</li><li>Distinct from 'Texian' (Anglo settlers) and 'Texan' (post-1836 residents)</li><li>Texican identity shaped by Mexican law, indigenous influence, and frontier life</li><li>Terminology reflects complex cultural and political histories</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Summarizing the key points ensures learners have a clear and accurate understanding of the term 'Texican' and its historical significance. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Recognizing a historical figure as a Texican helps contextualize their actions and loyalties during Mexican Texas.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Prepare to apply this understanding to explore Texican settlement and lifestyle next.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Failing to integrate terminology with cultural and historical context.</p></div></div>",
