    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">20</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Identity Reflection</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Learner Reflection: Word Cloud on Texican Identity</h2><ul><li>Reflect on key terms describing Texican identity</li><li>Consider cultural, political, and social aspects</li><li>Identify complexities and contradictions</li><li>Share words that capture your understanding</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This activity invites learners to synthesize their understanding of Texican identity by contributing words that reflect its complexity, helping visualize common themes and divergent views. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s13\">[13]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Words like 'Mexican,' 'frontier,' 'federalist,' 'Catholic,' and 'hybrid' may emerge.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Add 3-5 words that best describe Texican identity based on what you have learned.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Choosing overly simplistic or inaccurate descriptors without nuance.</p></div></div>",
