      "h": "San Antonio: A Microcosm of Texican-Anglo Relations",
      "body": "<p><strong>Why this deserves a deeper look.</strong> San Antonio exemplified the complex social dynamics between Texicans and Anglo settlers, where cooperation and conflict coexisted in a frontier town critical to Texas history.</p><p><strong>Source boundary.</strong> Teach this point from lauriemooremoore.com; legacy.education.texashistory.unt.edu. If a learner asks for a statistic, date, standard, or local procedure that is not in the knowledge base, Bernard and the presenter should mark it as a research gap instead of improvising.</p><h3>What to emphasize</h3><ul><li>San Antonio as a cultural and political crossroads</li><li>Texican families coexisted with Anglo settlers amid tensions</li><li>Shared defense efforts against Native American raids</li><li>Conflicting land claims and governance disputes</li></ul><h3>Worked example</h3><p>Texican and Anglo militias jointly defended San Antonio during frontier conflicts despite political disagreements.</p><h3>Practice and transfer</h3><p>Analyze how cooperation and conflict shaped community life in San Antonio.</p><p><strong>Common mistake to prevent.</strong> Viewing frontier communities as uniformly divided or unified.</p><p class=\"ref\"><strong>Source anchor:</strong> lauriemooremoore.com; legacy.education.texashistory.unt.edu <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup></p>"
